  "description": "¶Scope and Conventions Source: library/exploring-tilf-charges/doj-criminal-complaint.pdf (criminal complaint + supporting FBI agent affidavit).\nThis memo treats the complaint/affidavit as an allegation record, not as adjudicated fact. I use these labels consistently:\n[DOC]: directly stated in the source record (complaint or affidavit)\n[INF]: inference from [DOC] statements (flagged as inference)\n[GAP]: material missing from the record provided\nConfidence tags are epistemic judgments about the strength of support in the record, not about truth.\n",
